From Bm, Bharath (Nokia - IN/Bangalore) bharath.bm@nokia.com:
Just to add on top of Chethan’s analysis, the VMs which are not responding are OAM VM and CCP VM. Do we really have GTP path supervision running on these two VMs ? If so is it required to have the same since both OAM and Control plane would not have any user plane events (GTP events )being exchanged. If these do not have GTP supervision then we definitely will have the alarm raised from RAP since the GTP echo requests are not responded by these VMs. 
We now need to check from OAM as to why do we have IWF entries being added for these two VMs where we might not have user plane events being exchanged and hence would not require to have GTP path supervision for the same.
Excerpts from ICOM lookup table and the trs tpl events which adds IWF entries for these two VMs :
VM DEVICE ID = 57408, VM UDP PORT = 52152, PEER IP = 10.107.54.14
VM DEVICE ID = 57424, VM UDP PORT = 52152, PEER IP = 10.107.54.30

2018-06-04 00:02:04.512 { "In" : {'function' : 'TPI_NAMESPACE::icomgw::Proxy::addIwfEntry', 'parameters' : {, 'iwfEntry' : { "deviceId" : "57424", "localAddress" : "10.56.15.112", "remoteAddress" : "10.107.54.30", "remoteGtpfPort" : "52152" }}}}
Please check further from OAM on the IWF entries for OAM and CCP VMs.
